    "exposure_argument": "All rows lie on the affine line p(lambda)=lambda*p0+(1-lambda)*p1 with lambdas {1,0,x}.  The row-polytope endpoints are the min/max lambda rows.  The endpoint coordinate h=(lambda-lambda_min)/Dlambda is affine, lies in [0,1] on all rows, and h >= rho/D on rows at l1-distance at least rho. Since every signed row has l1 norm <= 1+2 delta, D <= 2+4 delta, so for delta<=1/4 and rho=4 tau, the margin is >= 4 tau/(2+4 delta) >= 4 tau/3 > tau/4=kappa.",
